x4freetext: Los Alamos Neutron Science Center/
Weapons Neutron Research (LANSCE/WNR)spallation
neutron source. The WNR neutron source at a 30-degree
production angle provided the continuous-in-energy
source of neutrons.
Neutron beam was produced by spallation
following the bombardment of a tungsten target by
800 MeV protons at the Weapons Neutron Research
facility (WNR) of the Los Alamos Neutron Science
Chemical form : 6LiF
Evaporated  onto a thin 0.84 mg/cm2 mylar backing
Typical target thickness :   1.0 mg/cm2
Target diameter 2 in
)four three-stage particle
telescopes, which  were variously positioned at eight
scattering angles during the experiment. Each telescope
consisted of a dE gas detector (20 torr of P-10 gas,
10% methane in 90% argon), followed by a Si dE detector
500 mu-m thick, and finally by a CsI detector. Reaction
products were stopped in Si detector
incident neutron energy was determined using
the time-of-flight technique, corrected for the
time-of-flight of the subsequent reaction product
detected.
Used for reaction product identification
Fission chamber located
16.32 meters from the source
